{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52965d79-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s955"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"955"},"text":"§ 955.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Practice of law restricted","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The clerk of each court and his deputies and assistants shall not practice law in any court of the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52965d7a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 646","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/926"},"text":"62 Stat. 926","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52965d7b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id52965d7c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., §§ 395 and 396 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231","children":[],"tail":", §§ 273, 274, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/1164"},"text":"36 Stat. 1164","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section consolidates parts of sections 395 and 396 of title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed. The remainder, relating to United States marshals and their deputies, is incorporated in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s556"},"text":"section 556 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Sections 395 and 396 of title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., have been extended to include all clerks, deputies, and assistants.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The revised section substitutes as simpler and more appropriate, the prohibition against practice of law “in any court of the United States.” (See reviser’s note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s556"},"text":"section 556 of this title","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For explanation of provisions omitted from sections 395 and 396 of title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., also see reviser’s note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s556"},"text":"section 556 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Changes in phraseology were made.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
